132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1268
H.P. 843 House of Representatives, March 25, 2025
An Act to Address Employee Recruitment and Retention Issues
Within the Maine State Ferry Service by Providing a Yearly Stipend
Reference to the Committee on Transportation suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative RAY of Lincolnville.
Cosponsored by Representatives: BECK of South Portland, EATON of Deer Isle,
FAIRCLOTH of Bangor, MACIAS of Topsham, WEBB of Durham.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 23 MRSA §4408 is enacted to read:
3 §4408. Stipend for employees
4 Beginning January 1, 2026, the Department of Transportation shall provide an annual
5 stipend to all employees of the Maine State Ferry Service calculated for each employee at
6 an amount equal to $5.00 per hour multiplied by the total hours worked in the previous year
7 for that employee.
8 Sec. 2. Prohibition to increase ferry tolls. Notwithstanding any provision of law
9 to the contrary, the implementation of this Act may not cause an increase in tolls under the
10 Maine Revised Statutes, Title 23, section 4404.
11 SUMMARY
1122 This bill directs the Department of Transportation, beginning January 1, 2026, to
1133 provide an annual stipend to all employees of the Maine State Ferry Service calculated in
1144 an amount equal to $5.00 per hour multiplied by the total hours worked the previous year
1155 for each employee and prohibits the department from raising ferry tolls to pay for the
1166 stipend.
